==Vevo==
Universal Music Group co-developed with Google<ref>{{Cite web |last=RouteBot |date=April 12, 2009 |title=Universal Music Group and Google Partner for Vevo |url=https://routenote.com/blog/universal-music-group-and-google-partner-for-vevo/ |access-date=June 5, 2022 |website=RouteNote Blog |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Announcing VEVO, a Partnership with Universal Music Group |url=https://blog.youtube/news-and-events/announcing-vevo-partnership-with/ |access-date=June 5, 2022 |website=blog.youtube |language=en-us}}</ref> [[Vevo]], a site designed for music videos inspired by [[Hulu|Hulu.com]], which similarly allows free ad-supported streaming of videos and other music content.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://exclaim.ca/music/article/universal_to_create_hulu-like_music_video|title=Universal to Create Hulu-like Music Video Site|access-date=August 10, 2016|archive-date=September 19, 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919164734/http://exclaim.ca/music/article/universal_to_create_hulu-like_music_video|url-status=live}}</ref>

On May 24, 2018, [[Vevo]] announced that it would no longer continue distributing videos to [[Vevo|Vevo.com]], instead opting to primarily focus on [[YouTube]] syndication.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nme.com/news/music/vevo-close-website-mobile-apps-2324374|title=Vevo to close website and mobile apps|last=Daly|first=Rhian|website=[[NME]]|date=May 24, 2018|access-date=February 6, 2019|archive-date=February 7, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190207020413/https://www.nme.com/news/music/vevo-close-website-mobile-apps-2324374|url-status=live}}</ref>

==Locations==
===Los Angeles metropolitan area===
====Santa Monica====
[[File:Universalmusicpublishinggroup.jpg|thumb|right|Universal Music Publishing Headquarters in Santa Monica, California.]]
UMG's operational headquarters are located in [[Santa Monica, California|Santa Monica]]. [[Interscope-Geffen-A&M]] and Universal Music Enterprises (UME), the company's catalog division, are headquartered in Santa Monica. [[Def Jam Recordings|Def Jam]], [[Island Records|Island]] and [[Republic Records]] also maintain offices there. UMG chairman & CEO [[Lucian Grainge]] is based at the company's Santa Monica offices. [[Universal Music Publishing]] is also headquartered in the city.

